data.description: Passive solar home with beautiful flagstone floor and attached redwood greenhouse on 2.4 acres with big views of Square Top. Built in the1990s by local custom builder Lincoln Frye for his family as a 3 BR 1 Bath, but two BRs do not meet current code for window placement. SS appliances, carpet, blinds, paint though out, bathroom remodel, and greenhouse renovation in 2012. An 1800 gal cistern and owned (not rented) 1000 gal propane tank. Well drilled in late 1970s not working. Setup for off-grid solar power with huge battery bank,48kW-hr battery bank. Low utility costs: heat house with passive solar and less than 3 cords wood, buy your propane from the cheapest source, almost no electric cost if you decide to use solar power. A small property on the back part of the property is included in this price! Pictures on listing are from 2017. More recent pics to come. Showings start Monday 12/11/2023.
